.\" manpage for simple_shell
.TH simple_shell 1 "15 April 2019" "version 1.0" "simple_shell manpage"
.SH NAME
simple_shell - Own simple hell project
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.RI "[""OPTIONS""]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
This shell is a copy created on C language, using the functions and system calls provided by the linux system. Simple shell allows execute some basics commands most the commands that are in the
.IR "PATH" ".
enviroment variable.
.PP
The simple shell can be run in interactive mode and non-interacctive mode, you can run this shell on
.IR "Linux Ubuntu 14.04.3 LTS" "
and was compiled with
.IR "gcc 4.8.4".

This shell implented functions that allows execute commands that are in the current dierctory, however, it has precedence if the executable file of the command is in the path indicated by the environment variable
.IR "PATH" ".
The enviroment variable is read at the begin of the execution, if you need add a new path for search your executables please modify the
.IR "PATH" " enviroment variable.

The options to execute commands in this sell is described below.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -1
Non-interactive mode, you can run any command using the follow notation (echo "COMMAND" | ./hsh"). In this case the shell will execute the command and return to the prompt.
.TP
.B -2
Interactive mode, execute the shell using the command ./hsh and once inside execute the command you need.
.SH EXAMPLES
The following are examples for run commands on the shell
.TP
.B
ls command
.PP
.RS
.BR $ " ./hsh"
.br
.BR " ls"
.br
#Makefile#  _strcat.c   exec.c         freelist.c       print_list.c
.RE
.PP
You can use the full path of the command:
.PP
.RS
.BR $ " ./hsh"
.br
.BR " /bin/ls"
.br
#Makefile#  _strcat.c   exec.c         freelist.c       print_list.c
.br
.PP
.RS
.BR $ " ./hsh"
.br
.BR " pwd"
.br
/home/vagrant/projects/simple_shell
.RE
.PP
You can use the full path of the command:
.PP
.RS
.BR $ " ./hsh"
.br
.BR " /bin/pwd"
.br
/home/vagrant/projects/simple_shell
.RE
.RS
.br
